		<item>
		<title>A-Star Raises $450M to Back Next-Generation Startups</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/a-star-raises-450m-to-back-next-generation-startups/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 15:41:49 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=201161</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>A-Star has raised $450 million at the final close of its third flagship fund. This highlights the less-is-more approach as it enters an era in which AI-drenched capital is doing</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/a-star-raises-450m-to-back-next-generation-startups/" data-wpel-link="internal">A-Star Raises $450M to Back Next-Generation Startups</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.a-star.edu.sg/News/astarNews/news/press-releases/a-star&#039;s-novel-ai-chip-design-platform-to-give-the-semiconductor-industry-a-boost-in-productivity-and-quality" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">A-Star</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> has raised $450 million at the final close of its third flagship </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/forus-raises-160m-to-advance-modern-medicine/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">fund</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. This highlights the less-is-more approach as it enters an era in which AI-drenched capital is doing the most.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new fund marks a considerable upward move from the company&#8217;s $315 million second fund raised in 2024, though it is still conspicuously spartan when measured against the $10 billion vehicles recently raised by industry intermediaries. The aim at A-Star is not to oversell the market but to overselect it.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Pedigree of Conviction</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A-Star was launched in 2020 by a trio of experienced operators and investors: Kevin Hartz, Gautam Gupta (ex-head of finance at Uber), and Bennett Siegel (ex-Coatue Management). Their combined histories include early support for decacorns such as Airbnb, DoorDash, Notion and Ramp.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Although it appears that a number of funds are entering into &#8216;safe&#8217; late-stage growth investing, A-Star remains firmly committed to early-stage investments, such as seed and pre-seed, where it usually aims to attain approximately a 10% equity stake. Investment checks range from $3 million to $10 million.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_201162" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201162" class="size-large wp-image-201162" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/AI-2-1024x853.jpg" alt="AI" width="1024" height="853" /><p id="caption-attachment-201162" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;We are not interested in the spray-and-pray model,&#8221; Hartz noted regarding the firm&#8217;s strategy. &#8220;Our focus is on a concentrated portfolio where we can provide genuine operational support to founders who are building the foundational infrastructure of the next decade.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/forus-raises-160m-to-advance-modern-medicine/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Forus Raises $160M to Advance Modern Medicine</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Teenager Thesis and Next-Gen Tech</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A very unique trait in the A-Star&#8217;s recent history has been its willingness to fund very young, green entrepreneurs. Hartz has been a famous supporter of investing in young, up-and-coming talent, with much of the group&#8217;s recent rounds directed at founders in their teens or early twenties.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new $450 million fund will focus on several key verticals:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>AI Infrastructure &amp; Agents:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Not just chatbots, but physical AI and autonomous enterprise agents. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Vertical SaaS:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Sector-relevant software to substitute existing legacy systems in complicated domains like logistics and defence.</span><b> </b></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Developer Tools:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Empowering smaller teams to build tiny-team unicorns through automation.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Recent bets from the firm include Krea, an AI-driven design tool, and Mercor, an AI hiring platform, both of which exemplify the firm’s interest in how artificial intelligence will fundamentally reshape the workforce.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Navigating a Bipolar VC Market</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The timing of the raise is strategic. Venture capital in 2026 has become a bipolar market: massive funds are pouring billions into foundational AI models, while the seed stage has seen a flight to quality as LPs (Limited Partners) demand more disciplined capital allocation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By capping the fund at $450 million, A-Star avoids the pressure to deploy massive amounts of capital into overpriced hot rounds. Instead, the firm plans to deploy this capital over the next three years, focusing on roughly 30 to 40 companies per fund cycle. This allows the partners to maintain a seat at the table during the critical early months of a company&#8217;s life.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As the industry watches to see if the &#8220;concentrated bet&#8221; model can outperform the &#8220;index the market&#8221; approach of the giants, A-Star is betting its $450 million that focused conviction is still the most valuable currency in Silicon Valley.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/a-star-raises-450m-to-back-next-generation-startups/" data-wpel-link="internal">A-Star Raises $450M to Back Next-Generation Startups</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
