		<title>Anduril Raises $5B in Massive Series H Funding Round</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/anduril-raises-5b-in-massive-series-h-funding-round/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 15:15:33 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=201157</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Anduril Industries has completed a $5 billion Series H funding round, helping it reach a $61 billion valuation. The new investment boost brings the company&#8217;s valuation up by 100% in</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/anduril-raises-5b-in-massive-series-h-funding-round/" data-wpel-link="internal">Anduril Raises $5B in Massive Series H Funding Round</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.anduril.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Anduril Industries</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> has completed a $5 billion Series H </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/forus-raises-160m-to-advance-modern-medicine/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round, helping it reach a $61 billion valuation. The new investment boost brings the company&#8217;s valuation up by 100% in eleven months after it hit the $30.5 billion benchmark in June 2025.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This round was led by Thrive Capital &amp; a16z (Andreessen Horowitz), indicating that defence tech has moved from a small side interest for venture goliaths to a core task for the largest capital pools. The oversubscribed round saw participation from existing investors Founders Fund, Sands Capital &amp; Counterpoint Global.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Scaling the &#8220;Arsenal of Democracy&#8221;</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The primary mandate for this new capital is the aggressive expansion of Anduril’s manufacturing capabilities. Central to this strategy is Arsenal-1, a massive manufacturing facility currently under development in Ohio. Unlike traditional defence contractors that rely on low-volume, high-cost production, Anduril is using its ArsenalOS software platform to treat hardware production with the speed and scale of consumer electronics.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_201158" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201158" class="size-large wp-image-201158" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Armoured-vehicle-1024x683.jpg" alt="Armoured vehicle" width="1024" height="683" /><p id="caption-attachment-201158" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The facility is designed to produce tens of thousands of autonomous systems annually, addressing what the company describes as a critical gap in the Western defence industrial base. By integrating design, simulation, and manufacturing into a single software-defined ecosystem, Anduril intends to provide the &#8220;intelligent mass&#8221; required for modern networked warfare.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/forus-raises-160m-to-advance-modern-medicine/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Forus Raises $160M to Advance Modern Medicine</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Financial Performance and Market Dominance</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Meanwhile, the money comes after a year in which Anduril has had an explosive financial expansion. It is believed that the company will have earned over $2 billion in revenue in 2025, around double the sum accumulated during the 2024 financial year. This scale of growth has been strengthened through major government contracts, such as a $20 billion enterprise deal secured with the Pentagon in March 2026. This 10-year contract is one of the largest single awards ever made to a non-traditional defence contractor.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Moreover, the Roadrunner, a vertical takeoff interceptor, has proven to be a commercial hit, netting more than 350 million dollars worth of orders. Its Lattice software platform continues to serve as the core of its product line, offering autonomous command and control capabilities through vehicles ranging from submarines to autonomous fighter aircraft.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Technological Milestones</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Series H announcement follows several recent technical milestones. In the last year, Anduril has completed an autonomous flight demonstration on the U.S. Air Force&#8217;s uninhabited combat aircraft program and supplied the first international program of record to the Royal Australian Navy.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Anduril has almost doubled its headcount over the past 12 months, seemingly making it the main challenger of old forces such as Lockheed and Northrop. While hearsay of a 2027 float persists, the company’s priority today is seemingly investing its $5B war chest in its infrastructure and R&amp;D pipelines before entering the public eye.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/anduril-raises-5b-in-massive-series-h-funding-round/" data-wpel-link="internal">Anduril Raises $5B in Massive Series H Funding Round</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
