</ol>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Beginners can start with templates instead of creating rules from zero.</span></p>
<h3><b>How to Invest</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">To invest with Coinrule, users connect an exchange, select a template or create a custom rule, define buying and selling conditions, set risk limits, and launch the rule. Users can adjust rules over time as their strategy becomes clearer.</span></p>
<h2><b>6. Pionex</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pionex is different from many crypto bot platforms because it is both an exchange and a trading bot platform. It offers built-in bots, which means users do not need to connect a separate third-party service to an external exchange.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This setup reduces the need for separate exchange integrations. Instead of managing API connections, users can trade and automate directly inside the Pionex ecosystem. The platform is especially known for grid bots and DCA bots, which are commonly used by crypto traders who want structured entry and exit strategies.</span></p>
