					<description><![CDATA[<p>The healthcare technology company Forus announced today that they have secured $160 million in newly raised investment funds. The new investment will be invested in the growth of the company&#8217;s</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/forus-raises-160m-to-advance-modern-medicine/" data-wpel-link="internal">Forus Raises $160M to Advance Modern Medicine</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The healthcare technology company </span><a href="https://www.forus-international.org/en/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Forus </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">announced today that they have secured $160 million in newly raised </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/casimir-raises-12m-for-quantum-energy-chip-launch/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">investment </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">funds. The new investment will be invested in the growth of the company&#8217;s artificial intelligence-powered network focused on uniting the disconnected links between doctors, pharmacists, payers and biopharmaceutical manufacturers in offering current medicines.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">For this funding round, a strong group of VCs, including Thrive Capital, General Catalyst, Accel, Bain Capital Ventures (BCV), Redpoint, BoxGroup, and Pear VC, invested. Previously called Tandem, the new Forus for 2016 plans to use the funds to expand its platform across additional medical specialties and as part of its plan to further embed itself within the U.S. healthcare system.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the &#8220;Last Mile&#8221; of Medicine</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Although drug discovery has sped up dramatically over the past ten years, thanks to breakthroughs in genomics and computational biology, the delivery of those treatments to patients has remained stubbornly archaic. On average, it still costs billions of dollars to develop a new drug and takes more than a decade to bring it to market. But even once the drugs have made it through the regulatory gauntlet, many patients are faced with another obstacle: a complex web of insurance authorizations and financial impediments that prevents them from actually taking their prescribed medications.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_201152" style="width: 490px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201152" class="size-full wp-image-201152" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Forus.jpg" alt="Forus" width="480" height="130" /><p id="caption-attachment-201152" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Forus</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Forus has established itself as the &#8216;missing layer&#8217; in the process. Integrating itself into physician workflows and electronic health records (EHRs), the platform automates the administrative process that occurs in the 3.5-minute lag period between a clinical decision and a patient actually getting their medication. This includes real-time benefits verification, prior authorizations, and the identification of financial assistance programs.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/casimir-raises-12m-for-quantum-energy-chip-launch/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Casimir Raises $12M for Quantum Energy Chip Launch</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Rapid Adoption and National Reach</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s growth trajectory has been notable, with provider adoption reportedly increasing tenfold year-over-year for the past two years. Currently, the Forus platform is used by thousands of medical practices and health systems across all 50 states. Data suggests that the network already supports patients in nearly 80% of U.S. residential zip codes, with a particularly high impact on patients suffering from complex or chronic conditions that require specialized, high-cost therapies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">For providers, the value proposition is centered on time reclamation. Traditional manual processes for medication fulfillment can take days or even weeks of back-and-forth communication between clinics and insurers. Forus claims to reduce this administrative burden by up to 70%, allowing clinical staff to focus more on patient care rather than paperwork.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A New Strategic Hub for Biopharma</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Beyond the clinic, Forus is becoming an essential partner for the life sciences industry. By providing unique insights into where prescriptions get stuck in the system and how patients drop off from treatment plans, the platform helps pharmaceutical companies design more efficient research and launch strategies. To date, five of the top ten global biopharmaceutical companies have already entered into partnerships with Forus to leverage this data-driven approach.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As the company looks toward the future, the goal is to ensure that the complexity of the healthcare system is no longer a limiting factor for scientific progress. With $160 million in fresh capital, Forus is set to continue its mission of making the most advanced medicines as accessible as common generic drugs.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/forus-raises-160m-to-advance-modern-medicine/" data-wpel-link="internal">Forus Raises $160M to Advance Modern Medicine</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
